Cell.Text: I owe you some answers, don't I?

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroTopic: Time to answer my questions.

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> Hmm. I guess that will have to do. You should pass for a real guest, at least until you open your mouth. | Ready to board the carriage to the embassy?
G|You can't go to a party at the Thalmor Embassy dressed like that.
Have you given Malborn the gear you want to smuggle into the embassy?

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineCarriageTopic: I'm ready to go.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Don't worry, it will all be waiting for you when you get back. | Just make sure you get back out of there alive with the information we need. | Good luck.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineCarriageReady: I'm ready. Keep the rest of my things safe for me.

Cell.Text: G|This is no time for cold feet. I've put everything in your hands here, not least Malborn's life. | Now do whatever it is you need to do, and let's get going before we miss our chance!

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineCarriageNotReady: Hold on a minute.

Cell.Text: [S] Good. I have your invitation to the party. | But the only way you're going to get past the guards is if they really believe you're an invited guest. | Which means you need to look the part, and not be armed to the teeth. Here, put this on.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineMetMalbornYes: Yes, Malborn's all set.

Cell.Text: G|You need to meet with him and give him whatever you think you can't live without while you're inside the embassy. | The Thalmor are paranoid and thorough. You won't get in the front door with anything but the clothes on your back.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineMetMalbornNo: Not yet.

Cell.Text: G|When you're ready, I'll keep the rest of your gear safe until you get back. | You'll only have what Malborn smuggled in for you, plus whatever you can pick up inside.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineExplainsCarriageRide

Cell.Text: I told you, I don't know anything else about it.

Node.Caption: MQ201PrisonerIntroTopic: I need to talk to you.

Cell.Text: What? Who... what do you want then?

Node.Caption: MQ201PrisonerIntroA1: I'm not here to torture you.

Cell.Text: [S] Fine. Whatever you want. Can't you just kill me and get it over with? | There's this old man. I've seen him around Riften. I don't know where he lives. I don't know his name. | Yes, he matches the description of this Esbern guy you're looking for. Maybe it's him. Maybe it isn't. | That's all I know, okay?

Node.Caption: MQ201PrisonerIntroA2: I'd like to hear it all one more time.

Node.ToolTip:
0003A1C5 - Custom, in use by kkuhlmann
Last User:kkuhlmann Date:4/5/2011 File:Skyrim.esm

Cell.Text: [S] Yeah, sure, okay. | Come on, this way. I've seen the guards use it to get rid of bodies. It must lead somewhere.

Node.Caption: MQ201PrisonerIntroB1: No time to explain. Let's get out of here. (Free him)

Cell.Text: G|Why don't you just kill me already.

Node.Caption: MQ201PrisonerIntroB2: You've been very cooperative. Thanks.

Cell.Text: G|Whatever you want. But let's go, now.
G|If you like. But we need to find a way to unlock that trap door.

Node.Caption: MQ201PrisonerIntroC1: Sounds good, I'll follow you.

Cell.Text: G|No problem. Thanks for springing me. I owe you. Look me up in Riften if you make it out.
G|I guess you know what you're doing. I've got to find a way out of here.

Node.Caption: MQ201PrisonerIntroC2: You go ahead. I'm not done here.

Cell.Text: [S] I damn well hope so. If it helps you twist them up, I'm glad to help. | They're after some old guy named Esbern. Something to do with dragons, I gathered from listening to them talk when they thought I was out. | I've seen a guy in Riften who they seem to think is him. | Not much to go on -- I don't even know where he lives, or his name. But they seemed pretty excited about it. | That's it. Now, let's get out of here.

Node.Caption: MQ201PrisonerIntroC3: Hold on. You may know something important.

Cell.Text: [S] I'm one of the last members of the Blades. | A very long time ago, the Blades were dragonslayers, and we served the Dragonborn, the greatest dragonslayer. | For the last 200 years, since the last Dragonborn emperor, the Blades have been searching for a purpose. | Now that dragons are coming back, our purpose is clear again. We need to stop them.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroA1: Who are you and what do you want with me?

Cell.Text: Go ahead. Whatever you want to know. Nothing held back.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroContinue: Yes, you do.

Cell.Text: [S] Not a damn thing. I was just as surprised as you when that dragon showed up.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroA2: What do you know about the dragons coming back?

Cell.Text: Really? Where?

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroA3: I've seen that dragon before, the one that got away.

Cell.Text: [S] Interesting. Same dragon... | Damn it, we're blundering around in the dark here! We need to figure out who's behind it all!

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroA3A1: It was the one that attacked Helgen, when Ulfric escaped from the Imperials.

Cell.Text: The first thing we need to do is figure out who's behind the dragons. | The Thalmor are our best lead. If they aren't involved, they'll know who is.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroA4: What's our next move?

Cell.Text: [S] Nothing solid. Yet. But my gut tells me it can't be anybody else. | The Empire had captured Ulfric. The war was basically over. Then a dragon attacks, Ulfric escapes, and the war is back on. | And now the dragons are attacking everywhere, indiscriminately. Skyrim is weakened, the Empire is weakened. | Who else gains from that but the Thalmor?

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntro2NewA2: What makes you think the Thalmor are bringing dragons back?

Cell.Text: [S] G|I'm not sure yet. I have a few ideas, but I'll need some time to pull things together... | Meet me back in Riverwood. If I'm not back when you get there, wait for me. I shouldn't be long. | Keep an eye on the sky. This is only going to get worse.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntro3Continue: So how do we get into the Thalmor Embassy?

Node.ToolTip:
0005F6F8 - Custom, in use by kkuhlmann
Last User:kkuhlmann Date:4/5/2011 File:Skyrim.esm

Cell.Text: What? Something you're still confused about?
G|Not here. Downstairs.
S|<<Shared>> I've figured out how we're going to get you into the Thalmor Embassy.
<<Shared>> I've figured out how we're going to get you into the Thalmor Embassy.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroRiverwoodTopic: Good to see you.

Cell.Text: [S] The Thalmor ambassador, Elenwen, regularly throws parties where the rich and connected cozy up to the Thalmor. | I can get you into one of those parties. Once you're inside the Embassy, you get away and find Elenwen's secret files. | I have a contact inside the Embassy. He's not up for this kind of high-risk mission, but he can help you. | His name's Malborn. Wood elf, plenty of reason to hate the Thalmor. You can trust him. | I'll get word for him to meet you in Solitude, at the Winking Skeever -- you know it? | While you're doing that, I'll work on getting you an invitation to Elenwen's little party. | Meet me at the Solitude stables after you've arranged things with Malborn. Any questions?

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroRiverwoodB1: So what's your plan? How do I infiltrate the Thalmor Embassy?

Cell.Text: If we could get into the Thalmor Embassy... it's the center of their operations in Skyrim... | Problem is, that place is locked up tighter than a miser's purse. They could teach me a few things about paranoia...

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntro3A1: So, we need to find out what the Thalmor know about the dragons. Any ideas?

Cell.Text: I saw guards dragging bodies over here. Might be a way out.
We've got to get out of here.
G|You saved my life. I won't forget it. Look me up if you're ever in Riften.
G|You didn't have to help me, so... thanks.

Node.Caption: MQ201PrisonerBlockingTopic: Are you all right?

Cell.Text: We need to find out if the Thalmor are behind the dragons coming back. We need to get into the Thalmor Embassy, somehow...

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntro3EntryTopic: What's our next move?

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> Exactly. Nobody even remembers our name these days. | We used to be known across Tamriel as the protectors of the Septim Emperors. Those days are long gone, though. | For the last two hundred years, we've been searching for the next Dragonborn to guide and guard, as we are sworn to do. | But we never found one. Until now.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroA4New: The Blades? Who are they?

Cell.Text: Before the Great War, the Blades helped the Empire against the Thalmor. | Our Grand Master saw them as the greatest threat to Tamriel. At the time, that was true. Maybe it still is. | So we fought them in the shadows, all across Tamriel. We thought we were more than a match for them. We were wrong.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntro2NewA3: Why are the Thalmor after you?

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> The faction that rules the Aldmeri Dominion. The ones who almost destroyed the Empire during the Great War, thirty years back. | There's no worse enemy to humankind in Tamriel. The Empire barely survived the last war. The Thalmor don't intend to lose the next one.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntro2NewA1: Remind me... who are the Thalmor?

Cell.Text: That would be a bad idea. I'd be too likely to attract the wrong kind of attention. But they don't know you at all, yet.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroRiverwoodA1: You're not coming?

Cell.Text: I've been doing this a long time, remember? While the Thalmor's been looking for me, I've been watching them.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroRiverwoodA2: That didn't take long.

Cell.Text: Don't worry about Malborn. He's not a dangerous character like you, but he hates the Thalmor at least as much as I do. | He's a wood elf - the Thalmor wiped out his family back in Valenwood during one of their purges that we never hear about. | Luckily they don't know who he really is, or he wouldn't be serving drinks at the Ambassador's parties.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroRiverwoodC1: Who's this contact of yours? You're sure I can trust him?

Cell.Text: So that's your plan, huh? Even if you could survive, by the time you got inside, whatever documents they had would be long gone. | We're there for information, remember? Trust me, I've been doing this for a long time. My way is better.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroRiverwoodA3: Why not just fight our way in?

Cell.Text: Let me handle that. You'll have a real invitation, don't worry. As long as you can act the part of a Thalmor toady, you'll get past the guards.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroRiverwoodC2: How am I going to get into this party?

Cell.Text: That's when the fun starts. You'll have to slip away from the party without raising the alarm. | Then you'll need to find Elenwen's office and search her files. Malborn should be able to point you in the right direction.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroRiverwoodC3: Once I'm inside the Embassy, then what?

Cell.Text: G|Sounds good. Be careful.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineIntroRiverwoodC4: I'll see you in Solitude after I meet Malborn.

Cell.Text: G|Awful damn cold up here. And only the guests are allowed inside. Damn foreigners and their inhospitable ways.
G|What are you out here talking to me for? Party's inside.
G|I'm paid to wait to take you home. Enjoy yourself.
G|The lady's already paid the fee. We leave when she gives the word.

Node.Caption: MQ201CarriageDriverBlockingTopic

Cell.Text: What did you tell him? Why did you do this to me?
You've got to help me! Please!
G|I don't know where I'll go. Somewhere far away from here.
G|Maybe this is a way out?
G|Maybe one of the guards had a key?
G|There's got to be some way out of here!
G|What did you tell him? Why did you do this to me?

Node.Caption: MQ201BrelasBlockingTopic2

Cell.Text: G|You must be new. We don't talk to each other here.
G|You here to see Rulindil, too, eh? None of my business of course.
G|Push off, will you?

Node.Caption: MQ201GissurBlockingTopic

Node.ToolTip:
000539C2 - Custom, in use by kkuhlmann
Last User:kkuhlmann Date:4/5/2011 File:Skyrim.esm

Cell.Text: [S] G|Oh... thank you. I don't understand what's happening. I can't stay here. What will I do now?

Node.Caption: MQ201BrelasPrisonerA1: Come on, you'd better get out of here. (Free her)

Cell.Text: G|What? Why? But... you must have said something to Erikur! You lied to him and now here I am! You're a heartless monster!
G|No... please, you have to help me! You don't understand what they do to people here!

Node.Caption: MQ201BrelasPrisonerA2: I can't help you right now.

Cell.Text: G|Go. Out. Before I change my mind.

Node.Caption: MQ201GeneralBlockingTopic

Cell.Text: Hey, haven't I seen you around the Flagon? I never expected to see another Guild brother down here. | They grabbed me in the Ratway. The nerve of these bastards... they need to be taught a lesson.
They grabbed me in Riften. They seem to think I know something. They just kept asking me the same damn questions.

Node.Caption: MQ201PrisonerIntroC4: Who are you? What are you doing here?
